	<body>
		<div class="stl_01">
			<div class="stl_02">
				<object data="[assessmentdomain]/Resources/PinPage/img_03.svg" type="image/svg+xml" class="stl_03" style="position:absolute; width:51em; height:66em;">
					<embed src="[assessmentdomain]/Resources/PinPage/img_03.svg" type="image/svg+xml" class="stl_03" />
				</object>
			</div>
			<div class="layer">
				<div class="stl_04 stl_05">
					<div style="position:absolute; top:6.1676em; left:3.7333em;"><span class="stl_06 stl_07 stl_08" style="word-spacing:0.0076em;">Is your child ready for kindergarten? &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:9.9421em; left:27.5793em;"><span class="stl_09 stl_10 stl_11" >Student First Name: [firstName]</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:11.1921em; left:27.5793em;"><span class="stl_09 stl_10 stl_12" >Student Last Name: [lastName]</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:9.7613em; left:3.7333em;"><span class="stl_13 stl_14 stl_15" style="word-spacing:0em;">Log on to ﬁnd out! &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:12.4421em; left:27.5793em;"><span class="stl_09 stl_10 stl_16" >Student Parent Code: [parentCode]</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:13.6921em; left:27.5793em;"><span class="stl_09 stl_10 stl_17" >Website: <a href="https://www.cliengage.org">https://www.cliengage.org</a></span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:17.9823em; left:6.0342em;"><span class="stl_18 stl_19 stl_15" style="word-spacing:0em;">What is &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:19.9743em; left:6.0342em;"><span class="stl_18 stl_19 stl_20">Progress &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:21.9663em; left:6.0342em;"><span class="stl_18 stl_19 stl_21">Monitoring? &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:17.9823em; left:34.0321em;"><span class="stl_18 stl_19 stl_22" style="word-spacing:-0.0029em;">Help Support &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:19.9743em; left:35.2406em;"><span class="stl_18 stl_19 stl_23" style="word-spacing:0.0496em;">Your Child’s &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:21.9663em; left:37.7156em;"><span class="stl_18 stl_19 stl_24">Learning &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:26.0983em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_25 stl_10 stl_26" style="word-spacing:-0.0026em;">Throughout the school year, students in your child’s &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:27.015em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_28" style="word-spacing:0.0039em;">prekindergarten classroom are being given special activities &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:27.9317em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_29" style="word-spacing:-0.0067em;">to help the teacher track their progress. The teacher looks &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:28.8483em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_30" style="word-spacing:0.001em;">at the results of this “progress monitoring” to determine &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:29.765em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_30" style="word-spacing:-0.0026em;">if students are developing the skills they will need for &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:30.6817em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_31" style="word-spacing:-0.0105em;">kindergarten and their later school years. &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:26.0983em; left:27.4426em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_32" style="word-spacing:-0.0013em;">As a parent, you are your child’s ﬁrst teacher—but &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:27.015em; left:27.4426em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_33" style="word-spacing:-0.001em;">sometimes it’s hard to know where to start. When &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:27.9317em; left:27.4426em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_08" style="word-spacing:-0.0014em;">you log on to CLI Engage to view your child’s progress &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:28.8483em; left:27.4426em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_34" style="word-spacing:0.0006em;">monitoring scores, you’ll ﬁnd a host of resources to &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:29.765em; left:27.4426em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_35" style="word-spacing:-0.005em;">help you learn more about how your child is growing &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:30.6817em; left:27.4426em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_36" style="word-spacing:-0.0079em;">and how you can help: &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:32.265em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_25 stl_10 stl_37" style="word-spacing:0em;">The CIRCLE Progress Monitoring tool helps your child’s &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:33.1817em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_31" style="word-spacing:-0.0109em;">teacher identify learning areas in which your child is &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:34.0983em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_38" style="word-spacing:0.0001em;">developing a level of understanding that is expected for his &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:35.015em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_29" style="word-spacing:-0.009em;">or her age. The tool also identiﬁes areas in which your child &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:35.9317em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_39" style="word-spacing:0.004em;">might need more targeted support and practice. &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:33.5234em; left:31.2893em;"><span class="stl_40 stl_07 stl_41" style="word-spacing:0.0078em;">Activities For &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:35.1367em; left:31.2893em;"><span class="stl_40 stl_07 stl_42" style="word-spacing:0.0556em;">You and</span><span class="stl_40 stl_07 stl_42" style="word-spacing:-0.0034em;"> Your</span><span class="stl_40 stl_07 stl_42" style="word-spacing:0.0556em;"> Child &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:37.515em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_43" style="word-spacing:-0.0039em;">If your child is meeting or exceeding the expectation for &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:38.4317em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_26" style="word-spacing:-0.0012em;">his or her age, this is called “meeting the benchmark.” The &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:39.3483em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_44" style="word-spacing:-0.0107em;">teacher will oﬀer additional supports to help your child &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:40.265em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_12" style="word-spacing:0.007em;">progress further.</span><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_12" style="word-spacing:0.263em;"> If</span><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_12" style="word-spacing:-0.0242em;"> your child</span><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_12" style="word-spacing:0.007em;"> needs targeted</span><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_12" style="word-spacing:0.007em;"> support &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:41.1817em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_24" style="word-spacing:-0.0061em;">for a particular skill, then the teacher might use a variety &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:42.0983em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_45" style="word-spacing:0.0034em;">of diﬀerent teaching strategies to support that area of &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:43.015em; left:3.45em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_34">development. &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:37.8947em; left:31.3em;"><span class="stl_40 stl_07 stl_15" style="word-spacing:0em;">Information on Child &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:39.508em; left:31.3em;"><span class="stl_40 stl_07 stl_46" style="word-spacing:0.01em;">Growth &amp; Development &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:45.7127em; left:5.2489em;"><span class="stl_47 stl_48 stl_39" style="word-spacing:0.0042em;">to view your child’s progress monitoring scores: &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:48.5123em; left:4.7333em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_43" style="word-spacing:-0.0015em;">Step 1: Using a computer or tablet, go to www.cliengage.org. &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:49.679em; left:4.7333em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_49" style="word-spacing:0.0017em;">Step 2: Click on “Sign Up” located on top right hand corner of the page. &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:50.8457em; left:4.7333em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_34" style="word-spacing:0.0023em;">Step 3: Complete sign-up information indicating you are a parent (you will need to use or create a google &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:51.7623em; left:4.7333em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_34" style="word-spacing:-0.0035em;">account to use as your user id for this site). &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:52.929em; left:4.7333em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_50" style="word-spacing:0.0042em;">Step 4: Once logged into the system, click on the blue “School Reports” buꢁon on the dashboard. &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:54.0957em; left:4.7333em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_08" style="word-spacing:0em;">Step 5: You will need to add your child by clicking the “My Connections” link in the green box on the leꢂ. &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:55.0123em; left:4.7333em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_12" style="word-spacing:0.0018em;">Click “Add Another Child” at the boꢁom and ﬁll in the required information. &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:56.179em; left:4.7333em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_51" style="word-spacing:0.0021em;">Step 6: Once your child has been added, click the “School Reports” link in the leꢂ green box. You can view &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:57.0957em; left:4.7333em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_35" style="word-spacing:-0.0007em;">the report by clicking on the orange icon to the right. If no report appears, contact your child’s teacher for &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:58.0123em; left:4.7333em;"><span class="stl_27 stl_10 stl_52">assistance. &nbsp;</span></div>
					<div style="position:absolute; top:60.8339em; left:16.9621em;"><span class="stl_53 stl_10 stl_32" style="word-spacing:0.0055em;">CIRCLE Progress Monitoring is a part of the Children’s Learning Institute &nbsp;</span></div>
				</div>
